    "Voice of Calm": {
        type: ["Interpersonal", "Social"],
        flavor: """
            <p><em>The argument had been escalating for five minutes. Two squad leads, nose to nose, over a supply dispute that had stopped being about supplies three sentences ago. The room was tense. People were picking sides.</em></p>
            <p><em>Springfield set a cup of tea on the table between them. The sound of ceramic on wood was very loud in the silence that followed.</em></p>
            <p>"Both of you have a point. Neither of you is making it well right now." <em>She sat down.</em> "Start over. One at a time."</p>
            <p><em>They started over. The tea went cold, but the argument didn't.</em></p>
        """,
        description: """
            <h3>Effects</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Your presence has a steadying effect on those around you. When tempers flare and situations spiral, you are the person who brings the temperature down, not through authority, but through composure.</li>
                <li>When performing a check that benefits from your calming influence (such as de-escalating a confrontation, steadying a panicking ally, or mediating a dispute), you can reroll up to two dice.</li>
            </ul>
        """
